HEADWORD: Biforine
<hw>Bif"o*rine</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>biforis</ets>, <ets>biforus</ets>, having two doors; <ets>bis</ets>
twice + <ets>foris</ets> door.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An oval sac
or cell, found in the leaves of certain plants of the order
<ord>Arace⟦ae⟧</ord>. It has an opening at each end through which
raphides, generated inside, are discharged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

